The paper applies techniques from argumentation theory and complex networks to model online discussions and predict the probabilities of winning arguments. This suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and social networks (cs.SOC) as well as natural language processing (cs.CL) and cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) which are all relevant to understanding and analyzing online conversations. Additionally, the paper's use of data scraped from an online debating platform suggests a focus on social informatics (cs.SI) as well.
